
## Setting up Heroku
heroku logs --tail
1. npm init  -- git init
  package.json --> add: 
    "engines": {
      "node": "VERSION CODE"
    },
    "scripts": {
      "test": "echo \"Error: no test specified\" && exit 1",
      "start": "node server.js",
      "watch": "nodemon server.js"
    },

2. heroku create

3.  process.env.PORT || 3000
    heroku --> settings --> config vars

4. git add .
   git commit -m ""

5. git push heroku master
